From 0db6a7a999a74cb22adc410345c876e2587ffedb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Sun, 28 Jun 2026 17:51:15 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 5/6] Phase B UX: redesigned Performance page with 3-tab layout
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Replaces the 6-tab layout with a coherent 3-tab structure that tells
a complete story: how did I perform, why, and what to do next.

Key Insights for Your Next Picks (always-visible card above tabs):
- Active learning signals with High/Medium/Low Impact badges
- Estimated pool point improvement per signal
- Upcoming must-win/must-not-lose team alerts with recommendations

Review tab (primary):
- Hero strip: Pool Points · Exact % · Outperformed Engine % · Override ROI
- Decision Review: expandable rows showing engine confidence, applied
  learning, override reason, lesson learned, context factors per match
- Override Intelligence: success rate bar, net delta, avg/override,
  last-N trend (✓ ✗ streak), recommendation block
- Exact Score Optimisation: visual bars, bias stats, profitable adjustment
- Next Picks Checklist: dynamic items linking to fixture pages

Learning tab:
- Signal cards: narrative + compact badges (matches, avg Δpts, confidence)
  each closing with a Recommendation block
- Blind Spots: ranked by improvement opportunity with prominent +pts potential
- Learning Timeline slot reserved for future phase

Diagnostics tab: unchanged model internals, leaderboard, calibration

Architecture:
- Shared performance-data.ts computes everything once (reviews, signals,
  qualMap, upcoming fixtures) — tabs receive typed PerformanceData props
- Learning Timeline extensible: slot comment in tab-learning.tsx
- All internal identifiers translated to human language

Co-Authored-By: Claude Sonnet 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
Claude-Session: https://claude.ai/code/session_01RU92kjKaNM5o2ZXbwgeazK
